The paper deals with the impact of channel reciprocity and channel estimation error on the performance of linear precoding in a TDD multi-user massive MIMO system. This involves topics related to information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), systems and control (cs.SY), multimedia (cs.MM), and computer communication (cs.COM). However, since the paper primarily focuses on the impact of channel reciprocity and channel estimation error on the performance of linear precoding, we can infer that cs.IT and cs.NI are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.SY, cs.MM, and cs.COM.
